<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98847426559964></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98847426559964><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=98847426559964>XP Rules X-plained</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Apr 28th 12:11 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The thing i hear a lot is that higher levels get more xp then lower levels. This is both wrong and right.<br><br>WRONG: From every kill all group members, regardless of level, will VISUALLY receivehte exact same amount of experience. So the ACTUAL numbers are different the Percentage of xp points to a whole level is the same.<br><br>RIGHT: The actual number of xp Points is different, but the relation of that number to the whoole is the same.<br><br><br>Conclusion is.If you try to avoid grouping with people f a higher level.. Dont! It doesnt hurtt you in any way, you get the same xp as if he was your level<br><br>Saialaa songtwister Minstrel of 53 season<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
