	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are a lot of various thoughts on this subject.  Since we are the jack of all trades, how can we ever possibly say which stat will benefit us.  That being said, you need to figure out what type of bard you will want to be.<br><br>Personally, I dumped all my points in CHA.  A guildie Bard and I argue about this topic all the time as he feels STR and AGI are key, but without having dbl attack, we can't even come close to the dmg other meleer's put out unless we have UBER weapons.  <br><br>Bare in mind, these are just my point, but I feel CHA will save your life way more often that AC, and CHA will do way more dmg than STR or dex.  CHA is key for many of our 'mind' altering songs.  At 52 I can still mez and charm certain mobs in Hate with another bard of higher lv not succeeding with the same %.<br><br>-Shaek, lv52 Bard, now with 181 unbuffed CHA :-)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
