<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98809053341133></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98809053341133><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=98809053341133>RE: instruments</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=46955><span id=Sage>aeriform</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>66 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 24th 1:35 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As indicated below, a mandolin and lute are both for stringed songs only, if you play any other song other than one requiring strings you'll just be singing, nothing more. I'd just stick with the mandolin for now.<br><br>Neither the mandolin or lute give you any noticable extra bonus except for when you play songs that are noted as being playable with stringed instruments.<br><br>There are several "unique" instruments available to you eventually. Some you have to camp or quest for. The following are the only intruments I'm currently aware of.<br>P-primary hand; O-off hand<br>b-brass; p-persussion; s-string; w-wind<br>n%-the approximate percentage added to the effect of the song<br><br>Brahms Horn ( 0.1 WT)<br>Pw	15%<br>Broken Minotaur Lord's Horn ( 0.8 WT, +10 SV POISON)<br>Pw	0%<br>Flute Mouth Piece ( 0.5 WT)<br>Pw	0%<br>Gypsy Lute ( 0.5 WT, +5 SV MAGIC) Lambent Breast Plate Quest Item<br>Ps	5%<br>Hand Drum ( 0.5 WT)<br>Op	0%<br>Horn ( 0.6 WT)<br>Pb	0%<br>Kelin's Seven Stringed Lute ( 0.6 WT, +9 AGI, +15 CHA, +9 DEX)<br>Os	20%<br>Lianna's Flute ( 0.5 WT)<br>Pw	0%<br>Lute ( 0.8 WT)<br>Os	0%<br>Lute of the Gypsy Princess ( 0.8 WT)<br>Os	5%<br>Lyssa's Darkwood Piccolo ( 0.5 WT)<br>Ow	35%<br>Mandolin ()<br>Ps	0%<br>McVaxius' Horn of War ( +9 INT, +15 CHA, +9 DEX)<br>Ob	0%<br>Minotaur Horn ( 0.1 WT)<br>Pwb	15%	<br>Mistmoore Battle Drums ( 0.5 WT)<br>Op	20%<br>Nostrolo Tambourine ( +5 INT)<br>Op	25%<br>Raw Bamboo ( 0.5 WT)<br>Pw	0%<br>Selo's Drums of the March ( 0.5 WT)<br>Op	35%<br>Sharkskin Drum ( 0.8 WT)<br>Pp	20%<br>Wooden Flute ( 0.5 WT)<br>Pw	0%<br><br>As for leveling Everfrost is nice. But I'd recommend doing some travelling and trying different mobs that may require different tactics and grouping with a some different players to get used to different playing styles. If you haven't already visited Kelethin, I'd head there. Try the dervish cutthroats in North Oasis for one or two levels, then try out Ocean of Tears or Lake of Ill Omen/Field of Bone (if you have kunark).<br>&nbsp;<br><br>Hope this helps,<br><br>Aeriform,<br>Tunare & Torv. Worlds</td></tr>
