	   <tr><td colspan=2>When I twist 3 or more songs, there will sometimes be "gaps" where an effect will stop a short time before it gets started again.  I don't mind this for heals, DoTs, and most other spells.  But I don't know whether haste spells give you your full advantage when there is a gap, or whether you lose the benefit if haste stops, even for a half-second, in the middle of a swing.<br><br>In other words, is a weapon's swing time reduced if haste is on at the start of the swing, or end of the swing, or does it have to be "on" for the entire duration of the swing to reduce the delay?<br><br>Right now, I am "double-twisting" haste with two other spells to make sure it never lapses.  e.g.:<br><br>haste<br>DoT<br>haste<br>healing<br>haste<br>DoT<br>haste<br>healing<br>etc...<br><br>Do I need to do this, or should I just twist haste in every 3 (or even 4) pulses and not worry about whether it has occasional lapses?<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
