<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98718650568549></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98718650568549><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=98718650568549>RE: Bard spells</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=31993><span id=Scholar>Taamas</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>61 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 13th 2:28 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.18]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>well to here it is:<br><br>bards have special spells, their called songs, heh. songs are special becuz they don't have a lasting effect, they last for "ticks" which is like 2 or 3 seconds. DoT, healing, buff and such songs are "tick" songs. they last for 3 "ticks" if not resung. <br><br>with that said, that is why many bards "twist". it depends on your connection (lag factor) and your xperience in twisting to determine how many songs you can twist. wit my crap connection i can only twist 4 songs. some are able to twist 5 wit cable or DSL. twisting songs not only improves your importance in the group, but adds to your groups strength.<br><br>the type of instruments are: wind, brass, percussion, string, and singing. their are unique instruments in each category that add a bonus to each song of that category. lute (string), flute (wind), hand drums (percussion), and horn (brass) are the regular instrument that do not add a bonus. they can be bought 5-7gp each at your local guild. wind is mostly mind-altering songs like charm, charismatic carillion, and invisibility. string are most of your songs that last for "ticks" like healing and DoTs. percussion are your speed and buff songs like selos or guardian rythmns. brass are the mostly the combat songs like fear and some DoTs. singing  is a weird skill since it requires no instrument, thus no singing song may have a bonus added on. they are your haste, strength, agility, and dexterity adding songs, also your clarity songs.<br><br>yes bards can "lure" a pet as you say. there are two different charm scenarios of NPCs. bards CAN charm a PCs pet in a dual, but CANNOT outside a dual or on PvP server (pretty sure bout the later). bards can charm a large number of NPCs. they mostly play crowd control when an enchanter is not present. bards get 2 charm songs (i think) one that doesn't require mana (lvl 27 song) and one that does (much higher lvl song). so yes bards can charm "a pet" as you ask, but only in duels on non-PvP servers.<br><br>hope that helped  =)<br><br>Taamas Starsinger<br>33rd Season<br>House of Wargoth<br>Saryrn<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
